<!--MOVEMENT ORDERS TABLES GO HERE-->
	<table border=0 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	<tr><td class=bodycopy>

<ol>
<li>The standard rules of regular Diplomacy apply, except where modified below.

<P><li>The following changes are made to the standard map:
<ol type=a>
<li>The supply center in Portugal is removed.
<li>Iceland and Ireland are passable spaces.
<li>New neutral supply centers are located in Bohemia, Iceland, Ireland,
    Livonia, and North Africa.
</ol>

<P><li>The victory condition is twenty supply centers.

<P><li>England begins the game with a fleet in Liverpool rather than an army.

<p><li>St. Petersburg is no longer a Russian home supply center, and Russia
   does not begin the game with a unit located there.

<p><li>An eighth power, Scandinavia, is introduced.  It begins the game
   owning the following supply centers and with the following units:
<center>
<table border>
<tr><th class=bodycopy bgcolor=#ff00ff><font color=white>Scandinavia</th>
	<td class=bodycopy><tt>Fleet Norway</tt></tt>
	<td class=bodycopy><tt>Fleet Sweden</tt></tt>
	<td class=bodycopy><tt>Army St. Petersburg</tt></tt>
</tr>
</table>
</center>

		<!--BODYCOPY ENDS HERE-->
	</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
	
